snippet.title: PE WITH JOE | BEST KIDS WORKOUT ROUTINES | #PEWITHJOE Joe Wicks (The Body Coach)
snippet.description:
We've been doing PE WITH JOE WICKS (#PEWITHJOE) for a whole week now and it has been a GREAT way to start the (home)school day! On Friday, Joe asked us to come up with a workout routine of our own...so here it is (instructions below):

With SIX KIDS, and the world on lockdown because of Coronavirus, we've been able to do the live exercise routines as a family, have fun, and stay fit. It was difficult for the first couple of days, and bodies were sore, but we persevered and have really enjoyed the FREE live PE lessons with The Body Coach (Joe Wicks).

THE BEVERLEY BUNCH #PEWITHJOE WORKOUT:

Hop Scotch - 30secs
Rest - 30secs

Push Ups - 30secs
Rest - 30secs

Kangaroo - 30secs
Rest - 30secs

Supergirl/boy - 30secs
Rest - 30secs

Star Jumps - 30secs
Rest - 30secs

Whale Wave - 30secs
Rest - 30secs

SpongeBob Square Twist - 30secs
Rest - 30secs

Spiderman - 30secs
Rest - 30secs

London Bridge - 30secs
Rest - 30secs

Skipping Rope - 30secs
Rest - 30secs

BREAK FOR TWO MINUTES
REPEAT EVERYTHING AGAIN.

Animal exercises for children and a fun educational video for kids with a trip to the Oakland Zoo. If you like toddler yoga, you will love RoboTots kids exercises video for children.

snippet.title: How to Relax Arm Stiffness: Exercises for a Child with Cerebral Palsy #003
snippet.description:
Meet Sebastian. He is a young boy with Spastic Quadriplegic Cerebral Palsy. His family wants to help me share treatment suggestions to help children like him across the world.  My clinic, Child and Family Development,  in Charlotte, NC, allowed me to use their facilities and their equipment to showcase Sebastian's skill and charming personality. We review techniques to reduce stiffness, encourage strength and control. I think you'll love spending time with him. Thank you to this family and my clinic for allowing this to happen.
 I also have available 3 children's educational books, "A is for Autism," "D is for Down Syndrome," and "C is for Cerebral Palsy" available on Amazon.  I have forthcoming "Pediatric Physical Therapy Exercises for the Hips".  If you have questions or suggestions, feel free to contact me at amysturkey@gmail.com. Please note: I am unable to provide treatment suggestions for a child I have not personally evaluated.

snippet.title: Dancing for exercise with the kids - Allen (4) and Rachel visit the MUVE-along Show
snippet.description:
www.muve.com. LIVE MUVE dance-along Show 02/21/11 (abridged). There is no school on President's Day, and that's why we get to dance exercise with little Allen (4) and Rachel today. Both love to MUVE and have no problem leading as a Muse. Maggie sets up a "Muse-Triangle" on the floor with stickers, and off they go. The person on the spot in the front creates the easy movement idea and the others follow "loosely." As always, you are invited to get a simple dance workout with us, right now, right here. A Muse-Triangle lies at the base of most MUVE Dancing Games (MDG.) These dancing games can be played with 2 or 22+ dancers. They make a fun physical activity for any party. MDGs can provide a quick break in between academic study periods right in the classroom! Anyone can do it, no matter the age or shape they are in, because all adjusts their movements to they own liking. If you want to see a whole school class dancing a MDG, check out http://www.muve.com/blog/school-muve  You can download the instructions to this and other MGDs from the muve.com website for FREE!
The first song is called "Banana Phone" by musical artist Rafi. Then we are groovin' to a Stevie Wonder song. Go ahead and do it! It is so much fun, just give it a try!

snippet.title: Head Control Scooterboard Ride Sitting: Exercises for a Child with Cerebral Palsy #017
snippet.description:
Meet Sebastian. He is a young boy with Spastic Quadriplegic Cerebral Palsy. His family wants to help me share treatment suggestions to help children like him across the world.  My clinic, Child and Family Development,  in Charlotte, NC, allowed me to use their facilities and their equipment to showcase Sebastian's skill and charming personality. We review techniques to reduce stiffness, encourage strength and control. I think you'll love spending time with him. Thank you to this family and my clinic for allowing this to happen.
 I also have available 3 children's educational books, "A is for Autism," "D is for Down Syndrome," "C is for Cerebral Palsy,"   and now 2 professional books "Pediatric Physical Therapy Exercises for the Hips", and "Pediatric Physical Therapy Exercises for the Knees" available on Amazon.  I have forthcoming "A is for ADHD" as well.  If you have questions or suggestions, feel free to contact me at amysturkey@gmail.com. Please note: I am unable to provide treatment suggestions for a child I have not personally evaluated.

snippet.title: Christmas Fitness Activity - 3 Year Old Santa Leads Dance Exercise for Kids
snippet.description:
www.muve.com. Allen inspires fellow toddlers, preschool and school children and parents on the lawn of the Hawaii State Art Museum with a dance along workout to the Christmas song Jingle Bells. Christmas time means good food and family fun. To stay healthy you can do some easy dance exercise moves right in front of the computer. See if little Santa Allen can get you out of your chair and into the Christmas spirit with this spontaneous and easy dance workout.

If you would like to see how to dance exercise at home go to muve.com and get the home workout beginner dance exercise DVD "Mellow MUVE." For more energetic inspiration get the "Family MUVE," a dance workout DVD with cardio exercises that are low impact in nature. Both DVDs feature everyday dancers from all age groups, from little kids to the elderly. And best of all, they all dance together to the same song, each in their own way.
